@* .NET 10 build hint: the presence of ANY .razor file in this project triggers the
   MSBuild logic that emits _framework/blazor.server.js into the static asset manifest.
   Without it, the legacy MapBlazorHub() path no longer serves the script and Studio
   loses all interactivity in .NET 10. We register no actual component here; the file
   exists purely to flip the build switch.
   See dotnet/aspnetcore#66059 + #66175 for the root cause discussion. *@
